{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:sirach.19",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 19 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:1",
      "text": "A labouring man that is given to drunkenness shall not be rich: and he that contemneth small things shall fall by little and little.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:2",
      "text": "Wine and women will make men of understanding to fall away: and he that cleaveth to harlots will become impudent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:3",
      "text": "Moths and worms shall have him to heritage, and a bold man shall be taken away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:4",
      "text": "He that is hasty to give credit is light-minded; and he that sinneth shall offend against his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:5",
      "text": "Whoso taketh pleasure in wickedness shall be condemned:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:6",
      "text": "but he that hateth babbling hath less of evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:7",
      "text": "Rehearse not unto another that which is told unto thee, and thou shalt fare never the worse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:8",
      "text": "Whether it be to friend or foe, talk not of other men's lives; and if thou canst not without offence, reveal them not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:9",
      "text": "For he heard and observed thee, and when time cometh he will hate thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:10",
      "text": "If thou hast heard a word, let it die with thee; and be bold, it will not burst thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:11",
      "text": "A fool travaileth with a word, as a woman in labour of a child.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:12",
      "text": "As an arrow that sticketh in a man's thigh, so is a word within a fool's belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:13",
      "text": "Admonish a friend, it may be he hath not done it: and if he have done it, that he do it no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:14",
      "text": "Admonish thy friend, it may be he hath not said it: and if he have, that he speak it not again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:15",
      "text": "Admonish a friend: for many times it is a slander, and believe not every tale.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:16",
      "text": "There is one that slippeth in his speech, but not from his heart; and who is he that hath not offended with his tongue?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:17",
      "text": "Admonish thy neighbour before thou threaten him; and give place to the law of the most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:20",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is all wisdom; and in all wisdom is the performance of the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:22",
      "text": "The knowledge of wickedness is not wisdom, neither at any time the counsel of sinners prudence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:23",
      "text": "There is a wickedness, and the same an abomination; and there is a fool wanting in wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:24",
      "text": "He that hath small understanding, and feareth God, is better than one that hath much wisdom, and transgresseth the law of the most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:25",
      "text": "There is an exquisite subtilty, and the same is unjust; and there is one that turneth aside to make judgment appear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:26",
      "text": "There is a wicked man that hangeth down his head sadly; but inwardly he is full of deceit,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:27",
      "text": "casting down his countenance, and making as if he heard not: where he is not known, he will do thee a mischief before thou be aware.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:28",
      "text": "And if for want of power he be hindered from sinning, yet when he findeth opportunity he will do evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:29",
      "text": "A man may be known by his look, and one that hath understanding by his countenance, when thou meetest him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.19.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:30",
      "text": "A man's attire, and excessive laughter, and gait, shew what he is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
